Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 5/30/00

Improved the error handling capability of the DPI code.  This includes
updating to the latest requant module, rewriting the bitstream parsing
module, and some picture level handling which disregard rate reduction
request for pictures with input errors.  Wayne also fixed some bugs in
the requant module and significantly reduce the picture breakup due to
input errors.

Changed DSP code to support new PPC features.  This includes the use of
different SPIDs in DSP-PPC communications for synchronized and asynchronized
messages.  Also a new message has been added to allow PPC to pass configuration
parameter to DSP.  With this feature we can turn on/off special features
of the DPI code by simply modifying an environment variable using the
bootloader.  Before we needed to generate different DSP codes to handle
each special case.

Working on the fix of the vertical sync problem that happens in the GI's
DCT 1000 setop box.

Attended the SCTE API group teleconference meetings.  Also met several times
with Joe Davis to discuss API issues that may affect our implementation.
Joe is our representative in the DPI group.

